# ActivateMode — mission_control_node → mode_manager_node.
#
# Asks mode_manager to drive every autonomy LifecycleNode through
# `configure` then `activate`, propagating the mission flag so each
# node selects the correct strategy (trackdrive / autocross / accel /
# skidpad).
#
# This is a one-shot service, not an action: mission_control awaits
# the response. Heartbeats during configure/activate are emitted by
# mission_control_node back to the supervisor on the StartMission
# action — this layer is fast enough that internal heartbeats are
# not needed.
#
# Mission values:
#   "trackdrive" | "autocross" | "accel" | "skidpad"
#
# Empty string deactivates+cleans up every autonomy node (used when
# the supervisor cancels Phase 1 to switch missions).

# ---------------- Request ----------------
string mission

---
# ---------------- Response ----------------
# True if every autonomy LifecycleNode reached `active` (or, for
# empty mission, returned to `unconfigured`).
bool ok

# Per-node diagnostic when ok=false. Empty on success.
string message
